<bibRefCitation box="[399,654,321,346]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1954 a) Estudios sobre Meloidae IV. Sobre algunos Mylabris Fabr. del Norteafricano. Eos, Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 30, 331 - 344." type="journal article">
Pardo Alcaide (
<number box="[573,633,321,346]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1954.0">1954</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
, were re-examined at 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:35275" box="[902,990,321,345]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:35275" name="Museo Nacional de Ciencias Naturales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">MNCN</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,249,922]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,357,382]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Description.</emphasis>
Body length: 
<quantity box="[509,642,357,382]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.275" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="0.95" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" unit="mm" value="12.75" valueMax="16.0" valueMin="9.5">9.5–16 mm</quantity>
; setae only black, but mixed golden and black on legs; antennomeres uniformly black, III almost twice as long as IV, XI less than twice as long as wide (
<figureCitation box="[1114,1196,393,418]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[167,1415,985,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[162,1425,977,1492]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Mylabris (M.) madani Escalera: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286158/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[1168,1196,393,417]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
A); pronotum clearly narrowed anteriorly and with evident fore transverse depression; elytra without black apical fascia and with four (
<number box="[160,176,465,489]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="2.0">2</number>
: 
<number box="[180,196,465,489]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="2.0">2</number>
) parallel spots (
<figureCitation box="[375,457,465,490]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[167,1415,985,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[162,1425,977,1492]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Mylabris (M.) madani Escalera: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286158/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[428,457,465,489]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
B); setated posterior portion of the mesosternal “scutum” widely extended on the whole posterior half of “scutum” (
<figureCitation box="[460,541,501,526]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[167,1415,985,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[162,1425,977,1492]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Mylabris (M.) madani Escalera: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286158/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[512,541,502,526]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
C); male gonoforceps in lateral view slender (
<figureCitation box="[1054,1135,501,526]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[167,1415,985,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[162,1425,977,1492]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Mylabris (M.) madani Escalera: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286158/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[1107,1135,502,526]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
E), fused ventrally in basal two-fifths (
<figureCitation box="[276,357,537,562]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[167,1415,985,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[162,1425,977,1492]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Mylabris (M.) madani Escalera: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286158/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[328,357,537,561]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
D); aedeagal distal hook slightly far from apex and clearly distanced from the proximal one (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[167,1415,985,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[162,1425,977,1492]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Mylabris (M.) madani Escalera: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286158/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,574,598]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,249,922]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,443,609,634]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Taxonomic remarks</emphasis>
. This species was sometimes confused with 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[989,1157,609,634]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schreibersi">
<emphasis box="[989,1157,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">M. schreibersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is sympatric in 
<collectingCountry box="[151,255,646,669]" name="Morocco" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Morocco</collectingCountry>
, and has a similar elytral pattern. It differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[805,966,645,670]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schreibersi">
<emphasis box="[805,966,645,670]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">M. schreibersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the following features: body relatively shorter; antennomere III ca. twice as long as IV, XI less than twice as long as wide; elytra without black apical narrow fascia; setated posterior portion of the mesosternal “scutum” widely extended on the whole posterior half of “scutum”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1436,249,922]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
The variation of elytral black pattern is represented in 
<figureCitation box="[805,885,789,814]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1513,1535]" captionTargetBox="[167,1415,985,1484]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[162,1425,977,1492]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Mylabris (M.) madani Escalera: A. antenna; B. elytral pattern; C. mesosternum; D. tegmen, ventral view; E. tegmen, lateral view; F. aedeagus, lateral view; G. spiculum gastrale, dorsal view. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/286158/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Fig. 
<number box="[856,885,790,814]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
B. One uncommon form with very elongate inner posterior spot was erroneously described as a distinct species (
<taxonomicName authority="Fabricius, 1775" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1775" box="[880,948,825,850]" class="Insecta" family="Meloidae" genus="Mylabris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tahari">
<emphasis box="[880,948,825,850]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">tahari</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but its synonymy was defined by 
<bibRefCitation pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refString="Pardo Alcaide, A. (1954 a) Estudios sobre Meloidae IV. Sobre algunos Mylabris Fabr. del Norteafricano. Eos, Revista Espanola de Entomologia, 30, 331 - 344." type="journal article">
Pardo Alcaide (
<number box="[253,314,861,886]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" value="1954.0">1954</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
